@kiln-firing-slot-booking
Feature: Kiln Firing Slot Booking
  As a studio member
  I want to book firing slots in the studio's kilns
  So that my work is fired on a date I can plan around

  Background:
    Given the studio has two kilns with published firing slots
    And a signed-in studio member

  # Why: Core booking path — the minimal complete definition of the feature.
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Booking a free slot succeeds
    Given a firing slot that is free
    When the member books the slot
    Then the booking should be confirmed
    And the slot should no longer be shown as free

  # Why: Availability is the entry point for every booking decision.
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Viewing availability shows only free slots
    Given some firing slots are booked and some are free
    When the member views slot availability
    Then only the free slots should be offered for booking

  # Why: Members must be able to release a slot they no longer need.
  @key-example
  Scenario: Cancelling a booking frees the slot
    Given the member has a booking more than 24 hours before the slot starts
    When the member cancels the booking
    Then the booking should be removed
    And the slot should be shown as free again

  # Why: The manager's servicing need from the brief — blocked slots leave the pool.
  @key-example
  Scenario: The manager blocks out a slot for servicing
    Given a firing slot that is free
    When the studio manager blocks out the slot
    Then the slot should be shown as unavailable to members

  # Why: Just-inside boundary of the assumed active-booking cap.
  @boundary
  Scenario: Booking while holding two active bookings succeeds
    Given the member already holds two active bookings
    When the member books another free slot
    Then the booking should be confirmed

  # Why: Just-outside boundary of the assumed active-booking cap — should be refused.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] A member may hold at most three active bookings at a time
  @boundary @negative
  Scenario: Booking a fourth slot beyond the active-booking limit is refused
    Given the member already holds three active bookings
    When the member tries to book another free slot
    Then the booking should be refused
    And the member should be told they have reached
      the booking limit

  # Why: Double-booking is the most likely conflict in a two-kiln studio.
  @negative
  Scenario: Booking a slot that is already taken is refused
    Given a firing slot that another member has already booked
    When the member tries to book that slot
    Then the booking should be refused
    And the slot's existing booking should be unchanged

  # Why: Bookings belong to their owner — another member must not remove them.
  @negative
  Scenario: A member cannot cancel another member's booking
    Given a firing slot booked by a different member
    When the member tries to cancel that booking
    Then the cancellation should be refused
    And the booking should be unchanged

  # Why: The assumed notice rule needs a refusal path so late cancellations are handled.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] Bookings may be cancelled up to 24 hours before the slot starts
  @negative
  Scenario: Cancelling inside the cancellation window is refused
    Given the member has a booking that starts in less than a day
    When the member tries to cancel the booking
    Then the cancellation should be refused
    And the member should be told the cancellation window has closed

  # Why: Two members racing for the last slot must not both succeed.
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Two members booking the same slot at the same moment
    Given a firing slot that is free
    When two members book the slot at the same moment
    Then exactly one booking should be confirmed
    And the other member should be told the slot is taken

  # Why: Servicing can collide with an existing booking — the member must not lose work silently.
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=low] Blocking a booked slot cancels the booking and the member is informed
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Blocking a slot that already holds a booking cancels it
    Given a firing slot with a confirmed booking
    When the studio manager blocks out the slot for servicing
    Then the existing booking should be cancelled
    And the affected member should be informed
